SpiderFoot

1. Overview
SpiderFoot is an automated OSINT & reconnaissance platform capable of scanning domains, IP ranges, emails, and more using 200+ modules.

Use Cases:
- Reconnaissance in bug bounty
- Digital footprint discovery
- Passive & active scanning
- Automating OSINT workflows

---

2. Key Features
- 200+ OSINT modules
- Web interface + CLI support
- Export results to JSON/CSV
- Passive and active recon
- Integrations with Shodan, VirusTotal, CIRCL, and more
- Relationship graph visualization

---

3. Installation
 Linux
git clone https://github.com/smicallef/spiderfoot.git
cd spiderfoot
pip install -r requirements.txt
python3 sf.py -l 127.0.0.1:5001

Docker
docker run -p 5001:5001 spiderfoot/spiderfoot

---

4. Usage
Open the UI:
http://127.0.0.1:5001
Create a new scan
Select modules (DNS, Whois, social footprints, leaks, etc.)
Start the scan and review results

----

5. Important Modules
Module	Description
sfp_dns	DNS enumeration
sfp_leaks	Email/credential leaks
sfp_shodan	Shodan integration
sfp_virustotal	Malware / reputation data
sfp_social	Social media profiling

---

6. Advanced Use Cases
Automated domain takeover checks
Mapping subdomains + analyzing leaked credentials
Correlating data across modules
Infrastructure relationship mapping
